{"name":"sysevent_email_action","description":"Manages email notifications sent to users based on certain events or conditions.","summary":"In ServiceNow, the `sysevent_email_action` object is used to manage and configure email actions associated with system events. This object allows administrators to define specific email actions that should be triggered when certain system events occur. These email actions can include sending notifications, alerts, or other types of email communications to specified recipients.\n\nKey aspects of the `sysevent_email_action` object include:\n\n1. **Event Triggers**: Defines the system events that will trigger the email action.\n2. **Recipients**: Specifies the email addresses or groups that should receive the email.\n3. **Email Content**: Configures the subject, body, and other content of the email.\n4. **Conditions**: Sets any conditions that must be met for the email action to be executed.\n5. **Scheduling**: Allows for scheduling when the email should be sent, such as immediately or at a later time.\n\nBy using the `sysevent_email_action` object, ServiceNow administrators can automate and customize email notifications to ensure that relevant stakeholders are informed about important system events in a timely manner.","attributes":[{"name":"message_list","type":"glide_list"},{"name":"action_insert","type":"boolean"},{"name":"action_update","type":"boolean"},{"name":"subject","type":"string"},{"name":"digest_template","type":"reference"},{"name":"sys_updated_on","type":"glide_date_time"},{"name":"type","type":"string"},{"name":"item_table","type":"table_name"},{"name":"sys_updated_by","type":"string"},{"name":"reply_to","type":"string"},{"name":"digest_separator_html","type":"html_script"},{"name":"sys_created_on","type":"glide_date_time"},{"name":"sys_domain","type":"domain_id"},{"name":"digest_separator_text","type":"email_script"},{"name":"sys_name","type":"string"},{"name":"from","type":"string"},{"name":"enable_dynamic_transl